{"id": "EUVD-2024-53846", "enisaUuid": "904d38cd-a484-341c-abbd-6e44cf1cf769", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nexfat: fix the new buffer was not zeroed before writing\n\nBefore writing, if a buffer_head marked as new, its data must\nbe zeroed, otherwise uninitialized data in the page cache will\nbe written.\n\nSo this commit uses folio_zero_new_buffers() to zero the new\nbuffers before ->write_end().", "datePublished": "2025-01-21T12:18:11", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:57:13", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/942c6f91ab8d82a41650e717940b4e577173762f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/98e2fb26d1a9eafe79f46d15d54e68e014d81d8c", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-57943"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-57943"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "53bb63cf-bfcd-398e-bf7f-d4f46256ec5b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.10"}, {"id": "6071be4c-b43e-3b57-9561-b1100e2db814", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.12"}, {"id": "7674a31a-aad5-3c1e-b771-968c76106a04", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "cac8cd3b-7eaa-33ce-9d0a-32827788c134", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "db4a9e94-f33e-3af6-8287-0b76f340d19d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6630ea49103c3d45461e29b0f6eb0ce750aeb8f5 <98e2fb26d1a9eafe79f46d15d54e68e014d81d8c"}, {"id": "dd3e5f9e-fc02-3e66-b68d-0b57a86261ac", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6630ea49103c3d45461e29b0f6eb0ce750aeb8f5 <942c6f91ab8d82a41650e717940b4e577173762f"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "16c687e9-66cc-3453-94a7-76eca067223d", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}